	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">mattmatteh wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">does the 6502 have an internal register for indirect addressing modes to store the pointer?</div><br />Yes. There has to be at least some register fed to the internal ALU to allow the effective address to be built up. Why do you need this? Are you doing a state-machine implementation of the 6502?<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">also, is there an internal register to hold the address for the address bus?</div>
<br />How to answer this in the most helpful way depends on what you are trying to do.

		

